@node "page1" "Goonies"          
 
@{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/32seonliner.png"}
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/g2sm.jpg"}
@{JLEFT}       
    One of my all time favourite movie, it's 41 years ago 1985 movie
    was released, at the time I did play it on C64 & ZX Spectrum and
    how many times I've watched the movie? yeahhh it has to be in
    top 5. Somehow game jumped over the Amiga platform...



@{JCENTER}
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/gcv.jpg"}
VHS cover
@{JLEFT}    
    Some reports are coming in that Spielberg is in on a sequel,but 
    don't hold your breath for too long... some say it's bs
    
    
@{JCENTER}
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/c64c1.png"}
Commodore 64 version







Now hold your pipes ;)






@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/1.jpg"}
The bone organ from the movie
@{JLEFT}       





@{JCENTER}
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/gn1.png"}
@{JLEFT}
     WTF are we gonna have the game for Amiga anyway!
     
     
     We have something going on for the Amiga...
     Marlox is making a MSX conversion for the Amiga and it looks
     really good and it's fun to play!
     
@{JCENTER}
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/gn0.png"}
@{JLEFT}     
     To the right is a first alpha demo and it uses scaled MSX gfx
     Now to the left 2nd demo Marlox has begun upgrading gfx
     marlox.itch.io/the-amigoonies
     
     You can play both old/new version 
@{JCENTER}     
@{" AmiGoonies 0.1 " SYSTEM "c:execute ag1script"} 
@{" AmiGoonies 0.2 " SYSTEM "c:execute ag2script"} 
Unpack & show folder
@{JLEFT} 





     Now if you are like me and want some more fun right now...
     
@{JCENTER}
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/screenshot1.jpg"}
@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/goonies/screenshot2.jpg"}
@{JLEFT}
     https://goonies.jorito.net/
     
     I found this to be the best version I could find and
     it's as fun as the AmiGoonies ;)
      
     If you follow link you find both Win/Linux versions,
     now I'm running on Linux and found it not so easy
     to get it run on fullscreen but install on Heoric Games
     app fixed this issue. 
     
@endnode



