@node "page3" "Return of SLL" 
         
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/32seonliner.png"}@{JLEFT}
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/sll/floppydd.png"}@{JLEFT}
  Return Of SLL 1988                       Track 1 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll1"}
                                           Track 2 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll2"}
  Code  Ghostrider                         Track 3 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll3"}
  Text  Kermie                             Track 4 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll4"}
  Music S.L.L Sten Lysholm Larsen Denmark  Track 5 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll5"}
                                           Track 6 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll6"}
                                           Track 7 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll7"}
                                           Track 8 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll8"}
                                           Track 9 @{"  " SYSTEM "hip files/sll/mod.sll9"}
  
                                           @{"off" SYSTEM "hip quit"}
  
  I was browsing in imp3 looking for a track for this issue ohhh wow... 
  I have very found memorys of this disk, this was often played on my 
  A500 around 1988 and forward...
  
  Jewels-ReturnOfSll.adf is in archive, I did not find a WHDL version
  
  It bring many memorys...
  
  Ackerlight/Speedball Intro @{" WHDL " SYSTEM "wbrun files/Ackerlight_Speedball/Acker"}
  
  Now on my memorylane I've put together from my memorys a game list ;)
  Got the WHDL version of them and Atari joystick plugged in, let's game 
  
  Alien Breed               So smooth gfx crazy feel to it
  Alien Syndrome
  Barbarian
  Battleships
  BattleSquadron
  Bionic Commando
  Cabal                     Very nice tune
  Defenders Of The Crown    This was crazy in the days
  Dr Mario                  All the games are so cool
  Fright Night              Pretty hard game but aren't they all?
  Fusion
  Future Wars
  Great Giana Sisters
  Hybris
  Insanity Fight
  It Came From The Desert   Ohhh what memories
  Lemmings                  Oh my good
  Menace                    Again my favourites
  North And South           They are crazy many nice games
  Obliterator
  Racter                    
  Rainbow Islands
  Red Heat
  RType
  Sarcophaser               This was my first Amiga game I've played
  Sex Machine               OR was it this one.... ;) now I'm not sure 
                            this is the actual game back then, there 
                            was only a dick and a meter but I can't 
                            find it...
                                                    
  Shadow Of The Beast
  Silkworm
  Speedball
  Stunt Car Racer
  SWIV
  Sword Of Sodan            This was also a totally crazy good game
  Venus The Fly Trap        Very nice tune in this one as many others
  Xenon
  Zany Golf                 It was and is damn slow on stock A500 and
                            still I played it like crazy
  Zynaps
 
  I'm not to include the games since they are commercial games...
  
  
                             These 3 disks are already in 32se distro
  His Masters Noice          @{" Open 32se folder " SYSTEM "win apps:Music Disks/"}
  Sound of Gnome             
  Megademo Red Sector Inc  
  
           
                                   * * *                       

@endnode 
 
 


@node "page4" "Curated fun"
 
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/32seonliner.png"}@{JLEFT}
  
  
      Curated fun for everyone... ;)
      
       
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/youngdefender.jpg"}@{JLEFT}

      Young Defender, AGA with fast mem
      Copyright © 1996 Eclipse Software Productions 
      
      I stumbled on this one in a PD archive, a nice shooter ;)
      
      Humanity is on the verge of intersellar exploration. The 
      perfect time for aliens intent on conquest to expand their 
      empire before man can improve his technology and therefore 
      his defensive capabilities.

      There is one ship with any hope of stopping the aliens. An 
      experimental design, there is only one trained pilot whose 
      age means he is lacking in combat experience. YOU are that 
      pilot.

      With Earth in such desperate need, you are called to duty 
      as your home planet's Young Defender.

      A mission briefing will be displayed before the start of 
      each level.

      Good Luck!
    
@{JCENTER}      
Open @{" Young Defender " SYSTEM "win GUIDEDIR:files/youngdefender/"} folder 
@{JLEFT}  
      Folder contains CD32 cover + ISO file, double click ISO






  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/wbtris.jpg"}@{JLEFT}

      WBTris
      Copyright ©1993 Dirk Böhmer & Ralf Pieper
      
      I like system friendly coding and this games works really
      good and is fun to play!
      
      Arrow keys + enter to dump
      
      
@{JCENTER}      
Unpack & show @{" WBTris " SYSTEM "c:execute game2script"} folder
@{JLEFT}
@endnode



 
 


@node "page5" "Norrland"
 
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/32seonliner.png"}@{JLEFT}
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/n10.jpg"}@{JLEFT}
      Norrland, AGA with 12MB free fast mem
      Copyright ©2026 Sami Vehmaa
      
      Story
       
      At 56 you took a chance on this undercover detective job! 
      Maybe you are too old for this...  Theres something going on 
      in northern parts of Sweden and you are here to uncover it all.
       
      As a undercover you need to maintain your normal delivery job
      and help out those living in outposts scattered around while 
      you investigate the death of a curior.
       
      You think, easy.... nope there is alot to keep track on like
      ammo, food, cold, dangerous animals...
      
       
      Game details
      
      · open world
      · adventure
      · survival
      · one player
      · light RPG elements
       
      In game
      
      · Joystick / Arrow keys + space
      · Fire button fires bullets
      · Hold fire for backpack + info (health, help etc.)
      · C display free chip
      · F display free fast
      · ESC displays options Save/Continue/Quit game
      
      In menu
      
      · V displays version & free memory
      · P changes game resolution 200/256 lines
      · Fire starts new game
      · 1 continue saved game
      
       
      8080.itch.io/norrland
      There is no demo DL on the page yet...
      
      This is a exclusive DEMO for you to try out!
      
      Some features are missing in demo like save game
      And game is still in development, this is not final!
      
      
@{JCENTER}      
Unpack & show @{" Norrland " SYSTEM "c:execute game3script"} folder
@{JLEFT}      
@endnode 




