@node "page7" "Me rambling"

  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/32seonliner.png"}@{JLEFT}
      pil cuman to issue 6 of 32se onliner
      
      I'm almost daily reading something crazy, where has the
      normal days gone ??? and the word/letters AI is smeared
      all over everything today...
      
@{JCENTER}
* * *
@{JLEFT}                               
  
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/doombuds.png"}@{JLEFT}
      doombuds.com just so you see I'm not joking
      
      So what the hell, earbuds has more power than a stock A1200
      now it's probably even faster than 030 at 50Mhz
      
      Earbuds are running Doom from 1993 at a decent speed 18fps
      
      Another perspective..
      
      Intel has released it's latest x86 Panter Lake at 1.8nm
      The last rev of 68060 was at 0.42µm that's 420nm 
      
      THAT'S WOPPING 233 times smaller, then you think but 68080
      then... Cyclone V FPGA 28nm (Intel CPU around 2009 32nm)
      Now I'm not to compare FPGA since they are more complex
      and this holds the speed back.
      
      Amiga is not advancing in the industrial speed... and no
      way in a leading position
      
@{JCENTER}
* * *
@{JLEFT}        

@{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/ps1.jpg"}@{JLEFT}
  
     PocketStorm FPGA+Pi displayed at Amiga40 Germany
     
     Developer Claude Schwarz
     
     On issue 3 I briefly mentioned it that it could be a big hit if it 
     was released!
     Now I'm been thinking ahead of things and while this setup is 
     really cool I think I have a idea!
     
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/nanto20k.png"}@{JLEFT}    
       
     Tang Nano 20k
     
     This is the board used in PocketStorm, now my idea might fit 
     with this board or a custom or whatever.
     
     FPGA with a single USB port
     
     FPGA is only to contain chipset and stream video data trough USB
     
     The other part where you plug in the unit may it be Pi5, PC, Mac 
     has a 68k+RTG emulator
     
     There could be optional bigger FPGA so a 68k would fit inside with 
     option to switch on/off     
        
     So on the "PC" the emulator get the chipset RGB feed and if chipset
     is in active state PAL/NTSC resolution then emulator displays
     the data to screen, if RTG is in use it will discard video data
     but Paula and all other data will still be in use ;)
     
     It should have maximum possible chipram on FPGA board with a 
     optional switch 2/8MB
     
     Fast RAM is provided by PC, now if the FPGA was to have a 68k
     option I'm not sure how fast RAM would work over USB interface
     
     
     Is it plausable ?  
     
@{JCENTER}
* * *
@{JLEFT}      
           
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/wedge07.jpg"}@{JLEFT}   
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/wedge08.jpg"}
Notice the DVD player
@{JLEFT} 
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/wedge09.jpg"}@{JLEFT}     
       
      ITX small form factor Amiga computer case
      
      You can Google it and it's on Cults 3D you find it. It's a crazy 
      build, it has a gfx card in it and it has 3 displays running, 
      there is a video showing it :)
  
      However the keyboard has wrong layout & Win keys :(
      
@{JCENTER}
* * *
@{JLEFT}    
  
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/amiga1600.jpg"}@{JLEFT}
  
      Amiga 1600 by EMD69
  
      It has PCMCIA port on the left, right side 2x 9-pin DSUBs
      Front CF slot, Gotek, Floppy
      
      Not much is revealed, but looking at the position of PCMCIA slot 
      & 9-pin Joy/Mouse ports and the name.. I'll say it's a A600
      motherboard in it. If it was something else, who would put a
      PCMCIA adapter in it ?? nobody!
      
@{JCENTER}
* * *
@{JLEFT}    
  
  @{JCENTER}@{IMG "GUIDEDIR:files/amigawl.jpg"}@{JLEFT} 
  
      I built my mini Walker some years ago, hand made. It was really 
      hard, I want to do a full size but that's in another level...
      
      Tech: Pi4 OC, front USB hub, original A1200 orange LED below
      USB port, theres a big slow rotating fan inside to keep it cool
      
@{JCENTER}
* @{"*" LINK "page2"} *
@{JLEFT}

           
@endnode




